<!-- FULL JOURNEY: WELLBEING IN PRACTICE -->
<section style="
  max-width:900px;
  margin:3.5rem auto;
  padding:2.5rem 2rem;
  font-family:'Poppins', sans-serif;
  color:#244646;
  background:#f6fbfb;
  border-radius:18px;
  box-sizing:border-box;
">

  <p style="
    font-size:12px;
    letter-spacing:0.08em;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    color:#319fa2;
    margin:0 0 0.5rem 0;
    font-weight:600;
  ">
    The Work in Practice
  </p>

  <h2 style="
    font-size:clamp(24px, 2.8vw, 30px);
    font-weight:600;
    color:#056367;
    margin:0 0 1.25rem 0;
  ">
    Wellbeing in Practice
  </h2>

  <h3 style="
    font-size:18px;
    font-weight:600;
    margin:0 0 1.25rem 0;
  ">
    Silhouette’s Café
  </h3>

  <p>
    Before formalising my work in preventive health and wellbeing, I founded 
    <strong>Silhouette’s Café</strong>, formerly <em>Silhouette’s Health Café</em>, a wellness-focused business rooted in accessibility, education, and everyday care.
  </p>

  <p>
    Silhouette’s Café offered 100% certified essential oils, herbs, diffusers, herbal coffees and teas, and thoughtfully curated wellness products designed to support emotional balance, stress reduction, and intentional living. For a period of time, I also operated a physical storefront in Dallas, Texas, creating a space where conversations about wellbeing were practical, human, and grounded, not clinical or performative.
  </p>

  <p>
    What began as a product-based wellness business evolved into something deeper:
    an understanding that <strong>prevention lives in daily choices, environments, and rhythms</strong>, not just programmes or policies.
  </p>

  <p>
    While Silhouette’s Café currently lives quietly within my wider work, it remains deeply relevant to my preventive wellbeing practice. It reflects the same values I bring to organisations and individuals today: sustainability, nervous system awareness, emotional literacy, and care that fits real life.
  </p>

  <p>
    Silhouette’s Café will be returning in its next iteration, integrated, intentional, and aligned with the broader <em>Live Inspired</em> philosophy.
  </p>

  <p style="margin-top:1.5rem;">
    <a href="https://www.marshakerrtalley.com/silhouettes-cafe"
       style="color:#319fa2;text-decoration:none;font-weight:500;">
      Learn more about Silhouette’s Café
    </a>
  </p>

</section>


<!-- FULL JOURNEY: WELLBEING BEYOND THE INDIVIDUAL -->
<section style="
  max-width:900px;
